# Smart-default rules — managed by the "Browser Picker Rules" app (browser-picker-rules).
# You can also edit by hand. Format:  enabled|||pattern|||label
#   enabled : 1 = on, 0 = off
#   pattern : plain text = substring match (catches a URL and all its child paths)
#             contains * or ? = glob match against the whole URL
#   label   : must exactly match a Label in browsers.conf
# First enabled match wins (top to bottom). Example (disabled):
# 0|||github.com/myorg/myrepo|||Chromium — Default
